### English Title:
US Homeland Security Secretary threatens Harvard with loss of international student admissions

### English Text Summary:
US Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem threatened Harvard University with the loss of its ability to accept international students unless it provides records of "illegal and violent" activities by these students. The department demanded detailed reports by April 30, 2025, or Harvard would lose its Student and Exchange Visitor Program (SEVP) certification, which is necessary for issuing visa applications. Harvard, which has 6,793 international students, stated it would not compromise its independence or constitutional rights. The department also canceled $2.7 million in federal grants to Harvard. The situation follows accusations of creating a hostile environment for Jewish students and reflects ongoing tensions regarding university policies and federal oversight.

